rfen.  aWhich crises did racism suffer through the struggles of black people in the German colonial empire? During the long 30 years of colonial politics, racism became a biopolitical and society-shaping paradigm. Ulrike Hamann shows which specific articulations of racism were current at which times, and how these were connected with colonial and national policies. The point of departure of the analysis is not in the first instance theories of »race« , but rather the resistance against these, through a postcolonial reading. From the writings of Mary Church Terrell, W.E.B. Du Bois and Duala Manga Bell, a panorama of the articulations of racism in Germany emerges - but also its social counter model.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Nov 2021) 0aImperialismxSocial aspectszGermanyxHistory. 0aRacismzAfricaxHistory. 0aRacismzGermanyxHistory. 4aBiopolitik. 4aDeutsches Kaiserreich. 4aDuala Manga Bell. 4aFrauenbewegung. 4aGeschichtswissenschaft. 4aHegemonie. 4aKolonialgeschichte. 4aKulturgeschichte. 4aMary Church Terrell. 4aPostkolonialismus. 4aRassismus. 4aSegregation. 4aUnvernehmen. 4aW.E.B. Du Bois. 70(DE-588)4073624-60(DE-627)1060919990(DE-576)209190973aKolonialismus2gnd 70(DE-588)4076527-10(DE-627)10445184X0(DE-576)209202130aRassismus2gnd 7aHISTORY / World.2bisacsh  aBiopolitics.  aCultural History.  aDisagreement.  aDuala Manga Bell.  aGerman Empire.  aHegemony.  aHistory of Colonialism.  aHistory.  aMary Church Terrell.  aPostcolonialism.  aRacism.  aSegregation.  aW.E.B. Du Bois.  aWomen's Movement.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus eBook-Package 2015z978311070098508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2015z9783110439687oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE 